RemoteProviderSingleImpl
public class RemoteProviderImpl
extends java.rmi.server.UnicastRemoteObject
implements java.rmi.server.Unreferenced, RemoteProvider

This is a server-side implementation for a RemoteProvider. It finishes the job off of delegating requests from the client to a real RawProvider. Creation date: (2000-02-17 13:07:36)

reportCallsOnAddress

public void reportCallsOnAddress(java.lang.String address,
                                 boolean flag)
                          throws javax.telephony.InvalidArgumentException,
                                 javax.telephony.ResourceUnavailableException
Forward the request on to the local RawProvider

Since we don't track which Frameworks monitor a call, only allow turning this on. Note that multiple Generic Framework clients may have registered for reporting of this call.

Specified by:
reportCallsOnAddress in interface RemoteProvider
Tags copied from interface: RemoteProvider
Parameters:

flag - true if reporting is to be enabled, false to stop events relating to the call.
Throws:

stopReportingCall

public boolean stopReportingCall(SerializableCallId call)
Eat request to the local TelephonyProvider

Since we don't track which Frameworks monitor a call, we should eat this message, even though that will mean any call once tracked will always be reported on. Note that multiple Generic Framework clients may have registered for reporting of this call.

Specified by:
stopReportingCall in interface RemoteProvider
Tags copied from interface: RemoteProvider
Parameters:
call - The handle on the call to turn state change reporting off for.
Returns:
true if the call is known, false otherwise
